* Boiling points of carbonyl compounds are **higher** than that of the **corresponding alkanes or alkenes having similar \(M_{r}\)**. Explanation: More energy is needed to overcome the **stronger permanent dipole--permanent dipole interactions between carbonyl molecules** than the **weaker instantaneous dipole-induced dipole interactions between alkane molecules** (or **alkenes**).
